dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is similar to CIFAR-10 but contains 100 classes with 600 images each. It is used for more fine-grained classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Y. Le
X. Yang
dcterms:description: CINIC-10 is a dataset that combines images from CIFAR-10 and ImageNet, consisting of 270,000 images at a spatial resolution of 32x32. It is designed for rapid experimentation and benchmarking.
dcterms:title: CINIC-10

dcterms:creator: Y. Le
X. Yang
dcterms:description: Tiny-ImageNet is a subset of the ImageNet dataset, containing 100,000 training images with a resolution of 64x64 across 200 categories. It is used for image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: Tiny-ImageNet
